commit 846a2ded6e52520b84da5fe4692c38b8830b5000
Author: Kenny Long <kenny.alan.long@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 15 23:07:43 2026 -0500

    fix(31-08): CreatureObject attributesOnSet callback const size_t -> unsigned int (BITS-03)
    
    Rule-3 blocking fix exposed once the AutoDeltaVector header became x64-compilable:
    CreatureObject.cpp:608 registers attributesOnSet as an AutoDeltaVector<Attributes::
    Value,CreatureObject>::setOnSet callback, but the member fn took (const size_t elem,
    ...). size_t == unsigned int only on 32-bit; on x64 size_t (8B) != unsigned int (4B),
    so the pointer-to-member type mismatched setOnSet's deliberately wire-stable
    (const unsigned int, ...) contract -> C2664. Retype the elem param to unsigned int
    in both the header decl and the .cpp def (elem is only used in an == comparison;
    no width assumption). Mirrors the 31-07 GroupObject members/memberShips callback fix.
    Verified: CreatureObject.cpp compiles x64 exit 0.
