Author: Kenny Long <kenny.alan.long@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 15 22:30:41 2026 -0500

    fix(31-08): pin AutoDeltaPackedMap/Set/Vector wire counts to uint32_t (BITS-03)
    
    Mirror the Task-1 AutoDeltaMap fix across the rest of the AutoDelta* family so
    every serialized count binds the existing 4-byte Archive overload on LLP64 x64
    (raw size_t = 8 bytes = overload-resolution FAILURE; the 31-05 defect class).
    Wire byte-identical to the 32-bit server; element put/get byte-unchanged.
    
    - AutoDeltaSet.h + AutoDeltaVector.h: m_baselineCommandCount / baselineCommandCount
      MEMBER size_t -> uint32_t; pack/packDelta size()/commands.size()/v.size() puts
      guarded with assert(<= UINT32_MAX) + static_cast<uint32_t>; static_cast<size_t>(0)
      placeholder -> uint32_t; unpack/unpackDelta count locals (commandCount, bcc,
      targetBaselineCommandCount, skipCount, loop indices) -> uint32_t so the skip
      arithmetic stays type-consistent (modular-identical to the 32-bit build)
    - AutoDeltaPackedMap.h: derives from the (already-fixed) AutoDeltaMap; its own
      internal_pack/internal_unpack count locals -> uint32_t + the placeholder ->
      uint32_t (countCharacter() returns int -> already binds the 4-byte signed
      overload, left as-is). Command::index stays unsigned short by design (a 16-bit
      net-traffic optimization, not a count).
    - #include <cassert>/<cstdint> in each
    - the include/Archive/AutoDelta*.h copies are thin forwarders to these src/shared
      headers, so both consumer include paths are fixed by these edits
    - verified: -Scope autodelta sweep (10 TUs incl. Server/SharedGroupObjectTemplate
      + UnicodeAutoDeltaPackedMap + the scratch instantiation TU) compiles exit 0,
      0 C2665/C2668 (was 8 from AutoDeltaSet.h + the AutoDeltaMap cascade)
