commit 1b6a98ff49a0003312dcd2ff0e55a8bd091fd5a7
Author: Kenny Long <kenny.alan.long@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 15 22:26:06 2026 -0500

    fix(31-08): pin AutoDeltaMap wire counts to uint32_t (BITS-03 / D-07)
    
    - baselineCommandCount MEMBER size_t -> uint32_t so its pack/packDelta/unpack
      puts/gets bind the existing 4-byte unsigned-int Archive overload on BOTH x86
      and LLP64 x64 (a raw size_t is 8 bytes on x64 -> overload-resolution FAILURE,
      a compile error not a silent wire widen; same defect class as 31-05's std::map)
    - container.size()/changes.size()/data.size() puts: assert(<= UINT32_MAX) then
      static_cast<uint32_t>; the static_cast<size_t>(0) baselineCommandCount
      placeholder -> static_cast<uint32_t>(0)
    - unpack/unpackDelta count locals (commandCount/targetBaselineCommandCount/
      skipCount/loop indices + the shadowing baselineCommandCount local) -> uint32_t
      so the unpackDelta skip arithmetic stays type-consistent (modular-identical to
      the 32-bit build where size_t was also 4 bytes)
    - #include <cassert>/<cstdint>; wire byte-identical to the shipped 32-bit server
      (counts were always 4-byte); element put/get (cmd/key/value) byte-unchanged
    - the include/Archive/AutoDeltaMap.h copy is a thin forwarder to this src/shared
      header, so both consumer include paths are fixed by this single edit
    - verified: ServerGroupObjectTemplate.cpp + both SharedGroupObjectTemplate.cpp
      compile x64 exit 0, 0 C2665/C2668 (was 744 from AutoDeltaMap.h)
