      compute a seconds-DURATION for a UI countdown (SwgCuiGroup/SwgCuiStatusGround);
      small value, explicit static_cast<unsigned int> (x64 C4244-clean).
    - SwgCuiGroup.cpp:269/272 -> DISPLAY. timerEnd/timerTotal retyped time_t ->
      unsigned int to match the getter return contract (they are seconds-durations,
      not timestamps); removes the time_t->long/unsigned int narrowings at the root
      (pixel-width math + CalendarTime::convertSecondsToMS(unsigned int)).
    
    Rule-3 blocking fix (same TU): GroupObject members/memberShips OnInsert/OnErase
    callbacks const size_t -> const unsigned int to match AutoDeltaVector's wire-
    stable const-unsigned-int callback contract (size_t==unsigned int only on 32-bit;
    on x64 the pointer-to-member type mismatched -> C2664 blocked the TU). Used ONLY
    as AutoDeltaVector callbacks.
    
    Both target TUs compile x64 exit 0.
    
    DEF-31-07: 2 unrelated std::distance->int C4244 (D-07/N2 class) logged, NOT fixed.
    DEF-31-07-AUTODELTAMAP: NEW pre-existing class-(B) escape (AutoDeltaMap.h
    Archive put/get(size_t) C2668/C2665, same defect class as the 31-05 std::map fix)
    flagged STOP-and-report -- multi-site serialization-width change in a shared
    external/ours template header, exceeds this plan's 4-task scope. NOT fixed here.
