    revert(25-01): back out frame-scoped reversal guard — mechanism falsified
    
    Reverts 7820aea50. Runtime capture (gl05, Debug) proves the cell-reversal
    guard is net-harmful and aimed at the wrong layer:
    
    - The "reversed" 2nd portal segment is the LEGITIMATE collision correction,
      not a spurious ping-pong. Suppressing it pins cell membership on the
      overshoot side while the body sits on the corrected side -> portal renderer
      culls wrong -> interior drops to skybox (Kenny: "popped back after a second"
      = a later clean frame re-syncs). Without the guard both segments apply and
      membership stays consistent (the ping-pong self-corrects).
    - The plan premise "first target cell is a safe resting state" is false: the
      first target is the overshoot.
    - The visible snap is a POSITION rewind in CollisionResolve (frame 7593: 4.04m
      vertical, setPosition_p), a different code path the cell guard cannot touch.
    
    Original CORNERSNAP _DEBUG instrumentation (a9b419daf) preserved for re-diagnosis.
