Author: Kenny Long <kenny.alan.long@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 16 16:48:48 2026 -0500

    fix(32-02): strip overlapping c0 register semantics for fxc_47 (X4016) — 2d_texture/functions.inc
    
    - vertex_shader_constants.inc:122 #pragma def(vs,c95,...) is rejected by
      d3dcompiler_47 at vs_2_0 (collides with its constant auto-allocator),
      emitting X4016 'c0' (FXC's first-register report, not the c95 slot).
    - Flip the existing Rule E gate kRuleEStripPragmaDef false -> true
      (decision-table bottom row: present AND D3DCompile rejects -> ON).
    - Runtime-safe: c95 {0.0,0.5,1.0,1/ln2} is uploaded every frame by
      Direct3d9_StateCache::setConstants() (StateCache.cpp:235-237), so the
      stripped compile-time prefill is not lost.
    - fxc_47 repro on the live-TRE rewritten include tree: Rule E OFF -> X4016
      (exact match to in-game FATAL 536bf21f); Rule E ON -> compiles clean.
    - Scope NARROW: #pragma def is in exactly 1 of 311 shader files; single
      gate flip fixes the X4016 corpus-wide. No regression to the 9 overrides
      or probe corpus (audit re-run). Rule D stays disabled; A/B/C unchanged.

