commit 02edecf2b856d91b4da5b5d59cd5a71011dfda21
Author: Kenny Long <kenny.alan.long@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 15 19:08:05 2026 -0500

    fix(31-04): apply stable hash-to-int contract to all pointer sort keys (BITS-02)
    
    - StaticShader/ShaderEffect/3 live D3D9 boot-path getSortKey/getTextureSortKey
      sites + 2 D3D11 buffer-data sites now use
      static_cast<int>(std::hash<uintptr_t>{}(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(ptr)))
    - int return type preserved on every site -> ShaderPrimitiveSorter::Entry
      (int field) + comparators + virtual interface + 4 plugin impls do NOT widen
      (no shared-header ABI cascade; D-06 review #3)
    - Replaces both the D3D9 direct pointer-to-int casts and the D3D11
      cast-to-uintptr-then-truncate re-truncation; full pointer entropy on x64
    - 6 sort-key TUs compile x64-clean (0 C4311/C4312/C4244); no #pragma disable

diff --git a/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_DynamicVertexBufferData.cpp 
b/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_DynamicVertexBufferData.cpp
