codex
One real x86-functional risk in `d9ee92088` is not allocation, it is pointer stride fidelity: the 
asm advanced by explicit `SOURCE_VERTEX_SIZE`/`SOURCE_DOT3_SIZE`, while the C++ port advances typed 
pointers with `++src`/`++srcD3`. I’m checking those struct sizes before deciding whether it can 
explain the measured heap spray.
